# ${name}

> ${description}

This project is a **standalone Foundry Hosted Agent** exported from a
[Kratos](https://github.com/kmavrodis/kratos-agent) use-case. It contains:

* `copilot-instructions.md` — the system prompt that drives the persona
* `skills/` — Markdown-defined skills (one folder per skill, each with `SKILL.md`)
* `mcp-config.json` — the MCP server map the agent connects to at runtime
* `mocks/packages/` — bundled local stdio MCP mock servers (only those the
  skills reference); empty when the use-case relies on remote MCP only
* `main.py` — a ~300 LoC standalone runtime built on the
  [GitHub Copilot SDK](https://pypi.org/project/github-copilot-sdk/) and
  Foundry's `InvocationAgentServerHost`
* `Dockerfile`, `pyproject.toml` — single-stage uv + Python 3.12 + Node 20
* `agent.yaml`, `agent.manifest.yaml`, `azure.yaml` — Foundry / azd manifests
* `infra/` — minimal Bicep (AI Project + ACR + App Insights)

---

## Quick start — local dev with `GITHUB_TOKEN`

The fastest way to verify the agent boots is using GitHub-hosted models.

```bash
cp .env.template .env
echo "GITHUB_TOKEN=$(gh auth token)" >> .env
uv sync
uv run python main.py
```

The agent starts on `http://localhost:8088` — `POST /invocations` with
`{"input": "Hello"}` to interact with it.

## Local dev with **BYOK** Azure AI Foundry

Update `.env`:

```bash
FOUNDRY_PROJECT_ENDPOINT=https://<resource>.services.ai.azure.com/api/projects/<project>
MODEL_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=gpt-4o-mini
```

Then `az login` and `uv run python main.py` — the runtime uses
`DefaultAzureCredential` to mint Foundry tokens automatically.

## Deploy to Azure as a Foundry Hosted Agent

```bash
azd auth login
azd env new <env-name>
azd env set AZURE_LOCATION eastus2
azd up
```

`azd up` provisions the AI Project + ACR + App Insights from `infra/`, builds
the container via ACR remote build, and registers it as a hosted agent on the
Foundry project. The agent surfaces in the Microsoft Foundry portal alongside
any other agents in the project.

