## How the runtime works

`main.py` reads everything from disk relative to `/app` (or `PROJECT_DIR`):

| File                            | Purpose                                                      |
|---------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| `copilot-instructions.md`       | System prompt — frontmatter is stripped at load time         |
| `skills/<name>/SKILL.md`        | Per-skill Markdown contract; auto-discovered by the SDK      |
| `mcp-config.json`               | MCP server map — passed directly to `mcp_servers` kwarg      |
| `apm.yml`                       | (Optional) APM dependency manifest, copied only when present |

Sessions are managed by the Foundry platform: when `FOUNDRY_AGENT_SESSION_ID`
is set in the request context, the SDK resumes that session; otherwise a new
one is created. No external state store is required.

## Customizing the persona

* **System prompt** — edit `copilot-instructions.md` (keep the YAML frontmatter
  intact if you want it preserved by re-exports).
* **Skills** — add or edit folders under `skills/`; each needs a `SKILL.md`
  with frontmatter (`name`, `description`, `examples`).
* **MCP servers** — edit `mcp-config.json`. Local stdio servers must be on
  `$PATH` in the container; HTTP servers can be referenced by URL with
  `${ENV_VAR}` expansion for tokens.

## Re-using your own Foundry resources

When the parameters `useExistingAiProject=true` and the
`existing*` parameters are set, the deployment connects to your own AI
Project, ACR, and App Insights without provisioning new ones. See
`infra/main.parameters.json` for the full set of overrides.
